snippet.textDisplay: I. LOVE. THIS. SHOW. The point of this show IS that it's meant to be similar to season 1 to show that Joe's life is a perpetual cycle of trying to find love (especially with his backstory we learn in season 2) HOWEVER, this season builds up our trust and uses our expectations to deliver one of the most unexpected twists I've seen in a long time as well as kind of turning the manic pixie dream girl archetype that Beck was completely on its head. The point of the show is that Joe isn't a psychopath, he is a child who was treated extremely poorly and has deep trauma which has caused him to become a fucked up adult and the full message wouldn't really get across with just one season/version of this story. Joe is on a constant quest for love and is so possessive because of his lack of it growing up. He definitely is insanely fucked up and his past doesn't excuse any of his terrible actions, but he feels guilt and empathy and part of his obsession of helping children in bad situations is to try and save them from becoming himself because by the end of the second season, he has fully comes to terms with hating himself. This especially is shown when he sees his traits in another person and is afraid of that person. I think this show is amazing and i watched all of season 2 in one sitting (took 10 hours but i would definitely recommend). Also there's a whole phenomenon of people who are insanely attracted to joe. (im gay and im STILL really attracted to his personality) the show does an excellent job of making it believable that all of these people love him and yet he can have the darker murder side. This is just my little rant cuz i love this show.
